eavy-duty diesel engines\n| Buyout of joint venture formed in 1988. Renamed Caterpillar Power India Private Ltd. Merged into Caterpillar India in 2008.\n|-\n| Eurenov S.A.S.\n| Chaumont, France\n| 2007<ref name=\"Caterpillar-Inc-Feb-2008-10-K\">{{cite web|url=http://pdf.secdatabase.com/1009/0000018230-08-000052.pdf |title=Caterpillar Inc, Form 10-K, Annual Report, Filing Date Feb 22, 2008 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =Mar 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.thomasnet.com/companystory/517555|title=Caterpillar Completes Acquisition of European Remanufacturing Company, Eurenov S.A|publisher=|accessdate=September 21, 2014}}</ref>\n|\n| Automotive component remanufacturing\n| Organized under Caterpillar Remanufacturing Services\n|-\n| Forestry Division of Blount International, Inc.\n| Portland, Oregon, United States\n| 2007<ref name=\"Caterpillar-Inc-Feb-2008-10-K\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.siteprepmag.com/Articles/Industry_News/BNP_GUID_9-5-2006_A_10000000000000198340|title=Caterpillar Announces Acquisition of Blount's Forestry Division and Transition of Pioneer Machinery to Six Caterpillar Dealers \u2013 Industry News \u2013 Site Prep|accessdate=September 21, 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120310065207/http://www.siteprepmag.com/Articles/Industry_News/BNP_GUID_9-5-2006_A_10000000000000198340|archivedate=March 10, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n| Blount International, Inc.\n| Timber harvesting and processing equipment, loaders and attachments\n|\n|-\n| Shandong Engineering Machinery (SEM)\n| China\n| 2008<ref name=\"Caterpillar-Inc-Mar-2008-8-K\">{{cite web|url=http://edgar.secdatabase.com/1067/1823008000110/filing-main.htm |title=Caterpillar Inc, Form 8-K, Current Report, Filing Date Mar 12, 2008 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =Mar 20, 2013}}</ref>\n|\n| Wheel loaders\n|\n|-\n| Lovat Inc.\n| Toronto, Ontario, Canada\n| 2008<ref name=\"Caterpillar-Inc-Aug-2008-10-Q\">{{cite web|url=http://pdf.secdatabase.com/1232/0000018230-08-000275.pdf |title=Caterpillar Inc, Form 10-Q, Quarterly Report, Filing Date Aug 1, 2008 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =Mar 20, 2013}}</ref>\n|\n| [[Tunnel boring machine]]s\n|2 April 2008: \"This acquisition is Caterpillar's entry into the rapidly expanding tunnel boring machine business, and it represents an excellent strategic fit for our companies and the customers we serve around the world,\" \u2013 Stu Levenick, Caterpillar group president.\n2 May 2013: \"We continuously evaluate our strategic portfolio to ensure alignment with our long-term strategy and have concluded the tunneling business no longer fits that strategy,\" \u2013 Stu Levenick.\n''Caterpillar Tunneling Canada Corporation (CTCC) have notified employees that it will exit the business and cease production at its facilities by mid-2014.''\n|-\n| Shin Caterpillar Mitsubishi Ltd.\n| Sagami & Akashi, Japan\n| 2008<ref name=\"Caterpillar-Inc-Aug-2008-10-Q\" /><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/pressRelease/idUS68184+26-Mar-2008+PRN20080326 | title=Caterpillar, Mitsubishi Heavy Industries and Shin Caterpillar Mitsubishi Announce | date=2008-03-26 | work=Reuters | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090905014118/http://www.reuters.com/article/pressRelease/idUS68184+26-Mar-2008+PRN20080326 | archivedate=September 5, 2009 | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n| Mitsubishi Heavy Industries\n| Construction equipment\n| Joint venture since 1963, after purchase of majority renamed Caterpillar Japan Ltd.\n|-\n| MGE Equipamentos & Servi\u00e7os Ferrovi\u00e1rios\n| Diadema, S\u00e3o Paulo, Brazil\n| 2008<ref name=\"Caterpillar-Inc-Feb-2009-10-K\">{{cite web|url=http://pdf.secdatabase.com/2353/0000018230-09-000063.pdf |title=Caterpillar Inc, Form 10-K, Annual Report, Filing Date Feb 20, 2009 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =Mar 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.streetinsider.com/Mergers+and+Acquisitions/Caterpillar+%28CAT%29+Acquires+Stoc