e/idUS68184+26-Mar-2008+PRN20080326 | archivedate=September 5, 2009 | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n| Mitsubishi Heavy Industries\n| Construction equipment\n| Joint venture since 1963, after purchase of majority renamed Caterpillar Japan Ltd.\n|-\n| MGE Equipamentos & Servi\u00e7os Ferrovi\u00e1rios\n| Diadema, S\u00e3o Paulo, Brazil\n| 2008<ref name=\"Caterpillar-Inc-Feb-2009-10-K\">{{cite web|url=http://pdf.secdatabase.com/2353/0000018230-09-000063.pdf |title=Caterpillar Inc, Form 10-K, Annual Report, Filing Date Feb 20, 2009 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =Mar 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.streetinsider.com/Mergers+and+Acquisitions/Caterpillar+%28CAT%29+Acquires+Stock+of+MGE+Equipamentos+&+Servicos/3767123.html|title=Caterpillar (CAT) Acquires Stock of MGE Equipamentos & Servicos|work=StreetInsider.com|accessdate=September 21, 2014}}</ref>\n|\n| Railroad equipment remanufacturing\n| Subsidiary of Progress Rail\n|-\n| Gremada Industries, Inc.\n| West Fargo, North Dakota, United States\n| 2008<ref name=\"Caterpillar-Inc-Oct-2008-10-Q\">{{cite web|url=http://pdf.secdatabase.com/1332/0000018230-08-000375.pdf |title=Caterpillar Inc, Form 10-Q, Quarterly Report, Filing Date Oct 31, 2008 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =Mar 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.reuters.com/article/pressRelease/idUS133430+16-Jun-2008+PRN20080616 | title=Caterpillar to Expand Remanufacturing Business With Acquisition of Certain Gremada | date=2008-06-16 | work=Reuters | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090908221856/http://www.reuters.com/article/pressRelease/idUS133430+16-Jun-2008+PRN20080616 | archivedate=September 8, 2009 | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n| Gremada Industries, Inc.\n| Remanufacturing transmissions, torque converters, and final drives\n| Organized under Caterpillar Remanufacturing Services\n|-\n| Twin City Signal Inc.\n| Hudson, Wisconsin, United States\n| 2008<ref>[http://www.rtands.com/newsflash/on-the-right-track-twin-city-signal.html On the right track: Twin City Signal \u2013 Railway Track and Structures] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120603105131/http://www.rtands.com/newsflash/on-the-right-track-twin-city-signal.html |date=June 3, 2012 }}. Rtands.com (August 28, 2009). Retrieved on 2011\u201303\u201317.</ref>\n|\n| Signaling, traffic control\n| Division of Progress Rail\n|-\n| JCS Co., Ltd.\n| Yangsan City, Kyungnam, South Korea\n| 2009<ref name=\"Caterpillar-Inc-May-2010-10-Q\">{{cite web|url=http://pdf.secdatabase.com/858/0000018230-10-000234.pdf |title=Caterpillar Inc, Form 10-Q, Quarterly Report, Filing Date May 3, 2010 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =Mar 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cat.com/cda/files/2007651/7/113009%20Caterpillar%20Announces%20Acquisition%20of%20JCS%20Co%20Ltd.pdf|title=Caterpillar Announces Acquisition of JCS Co., Ltd.|publisher=|accessdate=September 21, 2014}}</ref>\n| Jinsung T.E.C. Co., Ltd.\n| Seal technology\n|\n|-\n| GE Inspection Products\n| Erie, Pennsylvania, United States\n| 2010<ref>[http://www.progressrail.com/news-ge-transportation.asp Progress Rail Acquires GE Transportation's Inspection Products Business \u2013 Progress Rail Services]. Progressrail.com (March 2, 2010). Retrieved on 2011\u201303\u201317.</ref>\n| GE Transportation\n| Rail inspection products\n| Division of Progress Rail\n|-\n| FCM Rail Ltd.\n| Fenton, Michigan, United States\n| 2010<ref name=\"Caterpillar-Inc-Jul-2010-10-Q\">{{cite web|url=http://edgar.secdatabase.com/846/110465910040750/filing-main.htm |title=Caterpillar Inc, Form 10-Q, Quarterly Report, Filing Date Jul 30, 2010 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =Mar 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessweek.com/ap/financialnews/D9FI73L00.htm |title=Caterpillar unit buys FCM Rail |work=Businessweek.com |accessdate=September 21, 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160107161102/http://www.businessweek.com/ap/financialnews/D9FI73L00.htm |archivedate=January 7, 2016 |df=mdy }}</ref>\n|\n| Rail maintenance equipment leasing\n| Division of Progress Rail\n|-\n| Zeit Comercio e Montagem de Equipamentos Ltda\n| Curitiba, Parana, Brazil\n| 2010<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.progressiverailroading.com/news/article.asp?id=23263|title=Updates from Portec Rail, MGE, Eckert Seamans and ShipXpress|work=Progressive Railroading|accessdate=September 21, 2014}}</ref>\n|\n| Automation and electrical equipment for locomotives and other industries\n| Acquired by MGE, a division of Progress Rail\n|-\n| [[Electro-Motive Diesel]]\n| La Grange, Illinois, United States\n| 2010<ref name=\"Caterpillar-Inc-Jun-2010-8-K\">{{cite web|url=http://edgar.secdatabase.com/893/1823010000269/filing-main.htm |title=Caterpillar Inc, Form 8-K, Current Report, Filing Date Jun 1, 2010 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =Mar 20, 2013}}</ref>\n| Greenbriar Equity Group LLC, Berkshire Partners LLC, ''et al.''\n| Railroad locomotives and large diesel engines\n| Wholly owned subsidiary of Progress Rail\n|-\n| Underground Imaging Technologies, Inc. (UIT)\n| Latham, New York, United States\n| 2010<ref>[http://www.forconstructionpros.com/online/Acquisition-Positions-Caterpillar-to-Deliver-Subsurface-Imaging-and-Mapping-Services/1FCP16840 Acquisition Positions Caterpillar to Deliver Subsurface Imaging and Mapping Services] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711015908/http://www.forconstructionpros.com/online/Acquisition-Positions-Caterpillar-to-Deliver-Subsurface-Imaging-and-Mapping-Services/1FCP16840 |date=July 11, 2011 }}. Forconstructionpros.com (January 12, 2011). Retrieved on 2011\u201303\u201317.</ref>\n|\n| Geophysical services, specializing in providing three-dimensional representations of underground utilities\n| Organized under Cat Advanced Systems Division\n|-\n| Caterpillar Xuzhou Ltd\n| Xuzhou, China\n| 2010<ref>[http://www.chinaknowledge.com/Newswires/News_Detail.aspx?type=1&cat=CMP&NewsID=%2034871 China Business News: Caterpillar to buyout Caterpillar Xuzhou]. Chinaknowledge.com (June 29, 2010). Retrieved on 2011\u201303\u201317.</ref>\n| [[XCMG|XCMG Group]]\n| Construction equipment\n| Joint venture since 1995, will become wholly owned subsidiary Caterpillar Xuzhou\n|-\n| CleanAIR Systems, Inc.\n| Santa Fe, New Mexico, United States\n| 2010<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hawthornecat.com/readNews.htm?id=38|title=Caterpillar Emissions Solutions Expands Capabilities Through Acquisition of CleanAIR Systems|publisher=|accessdate=September 21, 2014}}</ref>\n|\n| Customized stationary aftertreatment solutions for internal combustion engines\n| Wholly owned subsidiary of Caterpillar Inc. organized under Customer Services Support Division\n|-\n| [[MWM GmbH|MWM Holding GmbH]]\n| Mannheim, Germany\n| 2010<ref name=\"Caterpillar-Inc-Nov-2011-10-Q\">{{cite web|url=http://pdf.secdatabase.com/1422/0001104659-11-060986.pdf |title=Caterpillar Inc, Form 10-Q, Quarterly Report, Filing Date Nov 4, 2011 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =Mar 20, 2013}}</ref><ref name=\"reuters.com\">{{cite news| url=https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSTRE69L1IF20101022 | work=Reuters | title=Caterpillar buys 3i's engine maker MWM for $810 million | date=2010-10-22}}</ref>\n| 3i Group Plc\n| Gas and diesel powered generator sets\n| will become part of Caterpillar's Electric Power division (formerly ''Deutz Power Systems'' division of [[Deutz-Fahr]])\n|-\n| [[Bucyrus International|Bucyrus International, Inc.]]\n| South Milwaukee, Wisconsin, United States\n| 2011<ref name=\"Caterpillar-Inc-Jul-2011-8-K\">{{cite web|url=http://pdf.secdatabase.com/2333/0000018230-11-000376.pdf |title=Caterpillar Inc, Form 8-K, Current Report, Filing Date Jul 8, 2011 |publisher=secdatabase.com |accessdate =Mar 20, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.caterpillar.com/cda/files/2846365/7/070811.Caterpillar+Completes+Acquisition+of+Bucyrus.pdf|title=Caterpillar Completes Acquisition of Bucyrus|publisher=|accessdate=September 21, 2014}}</ref>\n|\n| Surface and underground mining equipment\n| Transaction closed without issuing new equity on July 8, 2011, in firm's largest acquisition ever, valued at $8.8 billion.\n|-\n| [[Pyroban|Pyroban Group Ltd]]\n| Shoreham, UK\n| 2011<ref name=\"Caterpillar-Inc-Nov-2011-10-Q\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cat.com/cda/files/3027453/7/Caterpillar+Acquires+Pyroban+Statement+FINAL.doc.|title=Cat \u2013 Products & Services \u2013 North America \u2013 Caterpillar|publisher=|accessdate=September 21, 2014}}</ref>\n|\n| Fire and explosion prevention solutions for engines and equipment\n|\n|}\n<!-- Please input entries into the table chronologically by date of acquisition, most recent at the bottom -->\n\n=== Divestitures ===\n\nCaterpillar occasionally divests assets that do not align with its core competencies.\n\n<!-- Please input entries into the table chronologically by date of divestiture, most recent at the bottom -->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Sortable table\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Asset Divested\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Location\n! scope=\"col\" | Date\n! scope=\"col\" | Purchaser\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Products\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| Turbomach Division of Solar Turbines Incorporated\n| San Diego, California, United States\n| 1985<ref name=turbomachsunstrand>{{cite web |url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1985-04-20/business/8501230692_1_sundstrand-caterpillar-solar-turbines |title=Caterpillar To Sell Turbine Division To Sundstrand |first=Mary Holm |last=Ansley |date=April 20, 1985 |work=chicagotribune.com |publisher=Chicago Tribune |location=Chicago, Illinois, United States |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5uRfdpLRS?url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/1985-04-20/business/8501230692_1_sundstrand-caterpillar-solar-turbines |archivedate=November 23, 2010 |accessdate=November 22, 2010 |quote=Sundstrand Corp. plans to buy the Turbomach unit of Caterpillar Tractor